George Cuppaidge developed the relay system (named ^*BJorj^*N) that he and Ish were using when this week's deal was played. The main advantage that the Jorj system has over most relay systems is that it is relatively easy to learn and remember. The entire Jorj system is described in only 12 pages of system notes - quite a contrast to the several hundred pages that most "complex" systems require. George is eager to share his ideas and talk system with other relay players. If you would like to learn more about Jorj, please e-mail George directly:

